SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 2939
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE RIGGS.
6367H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 226, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to the statewide
transportation improvement program.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 226, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 226.036, to read as follows:
226.036. 1. Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, all planned
2 expenditures included in the statewide transportation improvement program (STIP)
3 shall specify the county in which each project is to be performed and include itemized
4 expenditures and expenses for each project.
5 2. After any project included in the STIP is completed, the department of
6 transportation shall submit an itemized expenditure report to each county with a
7 project located within its jurisdiction.
8 3. No later than January 1, 2027, and each year thereafter, the department of
9 transportation shall make a report to the general assembly detailing the department's
10 expenditures for projects in the STIP, which shall include an itemization of such
11 expenditures organized by county.
✔
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

